data.text:
Quarterly Honors

Quarterly honors designations recognize scholastic achievement of Olympic College students. Students who qualify for quarterly honors will receive a letter of commendation. Criteria for the awards include:

Completion of 12 credits at the 100 level or higher during the quarter for which the award is given

The grades for these credits must calculate in the overall GPA

Grade Point Average Requirements

Deans' Scholars: 3.5 to 3.89 college-level GPA

President's Scholars: 3.9 to 4.0 college-level GPA

Graduation Honors - Associate Degrees

Graduation honors recognize scholastic achievement of students who have completed a two-year associate degree.

President’s and Deans' Scholars designation are noted on the Commencement Program and the official student transcript.

Award Criteria:

Only credits earned at OC will count toward the award.

At least 24 GPA credits of 100 level coursework or higher must have been earned at OC

Deans' Scholars: 3.5 to 3.89 GPA. Deans' Scholars may wear a silver honor cord at Commencement.

President’s Scholars: 3.9 to 4.0 GPA. President’s Scholars may wear a gold honor cord at Commencement.

President’s Medal: 4.0 GPA. President’s Scholars who earn a 4.0 GPA will be awarded the President’s Medal at Commencement.
